# {{archaic}} The [[prickly pear]].
#:*'''1809''': The '''Indian fig''' is very different from other figs; when ripe, it is of an oval form, and of a colour inclining to yellow; it has a thick succulent rind, so covered with fine sharp prickles, as to render gloves, or some other substitute necessary, when peeling it. — James Grey Jackson, ''An Account of the Empire of Marocco'' (London 1809, p. 77)